body:
**Bug Description**
Verilator reports a mailbox type mismatch error when passing a parameterized mailbox to a constructor, even when the parameter types are identical. The error suggests that mailbox__TzX and mailbox__TzY are different types, but they should be the same type.

**Error Message**
```
%Error: tb.sv:45:15: Function Argument expects a CLASSREFDTYPE 'mailbox__Tz2', got CLASSREFDTYPE 'mailbox__Tz1'
                   : ... note: In instance 'tb_top'
   45 |         drv = new(mbx);   
      |               ^~~
        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html?v=5.039 for more assistance.
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```

Verilator Version: latest main
Platform: Linux


Minimal Reproducible Example
```
// Base transaction class
class BaseTransaction;
    function new();
    endfunction
endclass

// Parameterized transaction class
class MyTransaction #(parameter int WIDTH = 32) extends BaseTransaction;
    bit [WIDTH-1:0] payload;
    function new(bit [WIDTH-1:0] payload = 0);
        super.new();
        this.payload = payload;
    endfunction
endclass

// Driver class expecting specific mailbox type
class MyDriver #(parameter int WIDTH = 32);
    mailbox #(MyTransaction#(WIDTH)) mbx;  // Expects specific parameterized type

    function new(mailbox#(MyTransaction#(WIDTH)) mbx);
        this.mbx = mbx;
    endfunction

    task run();
        MyTransaction#(WIDTH) tx;
        forever begin
            mbx.get(tx);
            $display("Driver got transaction with payload: %h", tx.payload);
        end
    endtask
endclass

// Environment class - this is where the error occurs
class Environment;
    MyDriver#(32) drv;
    mailbox #(MyTransaction#(32)) mbx;  // This creates one mailbox type

    function new();
    endfunction

    function void build();
        mbx = new();
        // ERROR: The mailbox type from the declaration doesn't match 
        // what the driver constructor expects due to parameter resolution
        drv = new(mbx);  // This line will cause the mailbox type mismatch error
    endfunction

    task run();
        fork
            drv.run();
        join_none
    endtask
endclass

// Top-level testbench module
module tb_top;
    Environment env;

    initial begin
        MyTransaction#(32) tx;

        env = new();
        env.build();
        env.run();

        // Send a transaction
        tx = new(32'hDEADBEEF);
        env.mbx.put(tx);

        #100;
        $finish;
    end
endmodule
```
**Steps to Reproduce**

Save the code above to a file called tb.sv
Run: `verilator --binary --timing tb.sv`
Observe the mailbox type mismatch error

**Expected Behavior**
The code should compile successfully since both mailbox declarations use MyTransaction#(32) and should resolve to the same type.

**Actual Behavior**
Verilator reports a type mismatch error suggesting that mailbox #(MyTransaction#(32)) declared in the Environment class is a different type than mailbox#(MyTransaction#(WIDTH)) where WIDTH=32 in the Driver constructor.

